	<body>
		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 29" type="calendarDay" name="29" >
				<outline text="No offense please here, but seeing a few takes like this online and *this* is the “worst kind of tech “criticism”. It’s just as important to cover labor issues and exploitation when women are the bosses as when men are. https://t.co/OBf97i7yV4" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 21:30:32 GMT" tweetId="1409987676271366151" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409987676271366151" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I do agree with Paul on this, there are a million male Holmes. The solution isn’t to allow women to exploit more people, it’s to hold the men doing the same things as accountable. https://t.co/Qzh4xR33kf" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 21:32:09 GMT" tweetId="1409988080849674246" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409988080849674246" inReplyToId="1409987676271366151" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="“Female founder implosion stories” also cover companies that matter to lots of women. Those stories are important to tell! We should not be doing less of that, the media should just hold men to the same standards (as many women tech reporters have been trying to do for years)" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 21:35:01 GMT" tweetId="1409988802773340163" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409988802773340163" inReplyToId="1409988080849674246" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="What the actual fuck is the matter with this account. This is sick. This young woman wrote a brilliant and personal piece on something SO many young people have struggled with and all these ppl are now mocking and harassing her. It’s disgusting https://t.co/HQDA91yTpQ" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 20:15:02 GMT" tweetId="1409968673104621572" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409968673104621572" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text=".@deannaschwartzz is one of the most brilliant, empathetic, dogged young reporters. She wrote about young ppl being robbed of pivotal experiences during Covid. And these fucked up people online want to mock her for not having her first kiss. https://t.co/8NaR6nCSTb" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 20:20:17 GMT" tweetId="1409969993635090432" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409969993635090432" inReplyToId="1409968673104621572" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="I am so angry about what @deannaschwartzz is being put through. Is this the “welcome to media” experience we want talented young women in the industry to have to endure? It’s fucked up beyond belief. Please send love and encouragement to @deannaschwartzz https://t.co/xoKLYaaJmF" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 20:25:21 GMT" tweetId="1409971269429125120" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409971269429125120" inReplyToId="1409969993635090432" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="All these platforms need Waymo editors https://t.co/63znzoOTpL" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 18:53:34 GMT" tweetId="1409948171392880641" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409948171392880641" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Real Life is the one website where I think I can confidently say I’ve read everything on it. Just subbed to their newsletter too https://t.co/2OXnRIJuIb" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 17:44:20 GMT" tweetId="1409930750577700867" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409930750577700867" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I think about this meme @rebexxxxa made on a daily basis https://t.co/KWOGhLVB06" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:40:00 GMT" tweetId="1409914558685220865" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409914558685220865" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="A few young writers have messaged me lately about worrying their pieces aren’t definitive enough, or they worry other ppl are judging them for their work, and I just want them and everyone to know (to put it in the context of the meme), we have all done the Cheetos interview" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:49:28 GMT" tweetId="1409916939934134286" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409916939934134286" inReplyToId="1409914558685220865" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="I’m so grateful for the attention my stories get &amp;amp; the work I do now, but I’ve been slogging through the digital media food chain for 12 years. Sometimes it takes a while, and you have to write mortifying sponcon for a year that your byline is forever attached to 🥴 https://t.co/jFIikIPlS0" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:55:07 GMT" tweetId="1409918364613419008" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409918364613419008" inReplyToId="1409916939934134286" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="If ur worried your work isn’t perfect or you have to write up a bunch of dumb SEO hits for your job, don’t stress or let it define you. It’s the reality of digital media unfortunately, and just know most all of us (millennial journalists at least) have been there. No judgement💓" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:59:39 GMT" tweetId="1409919502825922566" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409919502825922566" inReplyToId="1409918364613419008" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="Once I interviewed for a tech reporter job right after I published a story on a man using his own shit to paint a portrait of Mark Zuckerberg. I was so embarrassed bc I wanted to be a “serious” writer. But that whole construct is dumb and those jobs haven’t existed since the 90s https://t.co/J28iUFOo2C" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 17:07:08 GMT" tweetId="1409921387444137990" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409921387444137990" inReplyToId="1409919502825922566" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Only thing I'd add to this is the role &quot;snark&quot;/gossip communities play in all this, pushing these narratives &amp;amp; tearing ppl down. So much &quot;drama&quot; that gets picked up by media is just hate campaigns bubbling up from GOMI-like communities pushing a narrative https://t.co/7pBoCruEMC" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:01:25 GMT" tweetId="1409904849773228032" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409904849773228032" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="This all ties back into a certain strain of &quot;accountability&quot; culture, which @cwarzel wrote a great piece on recently too  https://t.co/pbLwM0SEkE" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:03:08 GMT" tweetId="1409905281178296323" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409905281178296323" inReplyToId="1409904849773228032" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="Definitley read this whole piece by @rebexxxxa on influencer drama, such a smart comparison to horse race journalism. https://t.co/7pBoCruEMC https://t.co/1qWVcoRklU" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:08:04 GMT" tweetId="1409906524084858883" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409906524084858883" inReplyToId="1409905281178296323" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="NELK's monetization strategy (shunning ad revenue and productizing themselves) is a strategy that's increasingly pursued by creators, and gives YouTube even less of an ability to play kingmaker and police the platform https://t.co/ezxqsb7Ofe" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:54:55 GMT" tweetId="1409903215471071243" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409903215471071243" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Demonetizing channels (youtube's primary form of punishment) doesn't carry much weight when creators are making tens of thousands of $$ from more direct revenue streams https://t.co/ezxqsb7Ofe" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:57:19 GMT" tweetId="1409903817953402887" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409903817953402887" inReplyToId="1409903215471071243" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="They're multiplying https://t.co/4fs2CXOTEA" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:52:10 GMT" tweetId="1409902520969826305" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409902520969826305" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@kathrynfiona wrote about the Glitch Queen https://t.co/LYsJCJMKkc" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:45:00 GMT" tweetId="1409900716957782017" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409900716957782017" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Oh great https://t.co/up9M5l8oLv https://t.co/4RfD3RL0il" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:13:00 GMT" tweetId="1409892663885770752" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409892663885770752" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Given FB's history of incentivizing certain people and content on the platform for years, I'm eager to see how well this line ages https://t.co/nSPVS7YP1u https://t.co/b417DS8mGn" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:05:00 GMT" tweetId="1409890651173494784" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409890651173494784" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I wrote about NELK, some of the top earning creators on YouTube, who take zero money from YouTube  https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:10:58 GMT" tweetId="1409877053466349569" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409877053466349569" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="The NELK boys are set to make over $70M from merch alone this year, their Happy Dad seltzer line is causing mobs outside liquor stores across California, they have a wildly popular proprietary subscription platform, and more. https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:19:00 GMT" tweetId="1409879075825586186" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409879075825586186" inReplyToId="1409877053466349569" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="We’re not going to sacrifice our content or change to make $500,000 a month from YouTube. Maybe in the short term we’re not buying Lambos like other YouTubers, but we could have a multibillion-dollar business on our hands.” https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:19:56 GMT" tweetId="1409879309221871620" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409879309221871620" inReplyToId="1409879075825586186" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="“With our audience, we can build pretty much anything. Maybe we start a men’s grooming company or we could sell condoms if we wanted to. We could open Full Send gyms. We could do pizza delivery.” https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:21:59 GMT" tweetId="1409879826106880014" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409879826106880014" inReplyToId="1409879309221871620" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="Shahidi imagines Nelk someday competing with multinational corporations like Amazon, Anheuser Bush, Apple, and Uber. &quot;Nelk could have an entire network of drivers that can eventually deliver anything that’s in our ecosystem.&quot; https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:23:39 GMT" tweetId="1409880246929743877" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409880246929743877" inReplyToId="1409879826106880014" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="This is definitely TMI and I will prob delete, but I’m honestly so proud and I want to share it. Something ppl might not know is I have very bad trichotillomania &amp;amp; dermatillomania and this is the first time in my entire life that I haven’t had an open wound on my head" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 05:29:53 GMT" tweetId="1409745917322817536" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409745917322817536" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I know that’s so gross, trust me I’ve felt ashamed about it my whole life. I have several bald spots on my head that will never grow hair back I’ve picked them so bad. Anyway I have ZERO wounds rn and haven’t pulled in a month. If u deal with this too know that it IS possible 💓" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 05:32:50 GMT" tweetId="1409746662583508995" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409746662583508995" inReplyToId="1409745917322817536" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Great interview with @mekosoff about the realities of the media industry and not tying your self worth to some digital media job https://t.co/p0oKMYyo5D by @bradesposito https://t.co/6rj8pjVcBw" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 05:18:36 GMT" tweetId="1409743080756965380" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409743080756965380" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="How it started, how it's going https://t.co/Fa1RHPEwKF" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 04:19:07 GMT" tweetId="1409728111382462468" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409728111382462468" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 28" type="calendarDay" name="28" >
				<outline text="HBD @holy_schnitt ✨🍾🎈" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 23:21:29 GMT" tweetId="1409653206108438532" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409653206108438532" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="California’s yoga, wellness and spirituality community has a QAnon problem https://t.co/phLE0MRN1B" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 20:41:17 GMT" tweetId="1409612892094095365" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409612892094095365" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="So impressed with @theinformation @kyurieff really useful Creator Economy startup database. I'm sure they'll be adding lots more as this sector continue to boom https://t.co/6DVeMk8vOo" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 20:01:19 GMT" tweetId="1409602833968635911" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409602833968635911" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="BI's @arperelli @dwhate @SydneyKBradley @margauxmaccoll have also made some excellent databases/lists that are totally worth the sub! Here's one they did of top investors/VCs in the influencer industry feat @ljin18 @rex_woodbury @conniechan and more! https://t.co/gfHmbbwIkN" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 20:06:14 GMT" tweetId="1409604071930044421" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409604071930044421" inReplyToId="1409602833968635911" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="&quot;Saying Near 'took their life' is giving these people an out for their actions, which directly resulted in the intentional death of a person.&quot; https://t.co/oqXRKoOjbl" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:43:30 GMT" tweetId="1409598349787893762" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409598349787893762" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="There's no such thing as a coincidence, the fact that you're reading this tweet means you're energetically aligned with me and this message" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:37:11 GMT" tweetId="1409596761098768393" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409596761098768393" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Let him do it https://t.co/Vpa8LCIGeb" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:36:46 GMT" tweetId="1409596654089478145" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409596654089478145" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@kathrynfiona on the digital-media-to-Netflix pipeline and more https://t.co/Ut5UpG4iBG" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:28:57 GMT" tweetId="1409594688588365824" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409594688588365824" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Only in the past year has the tech industry as a whole started to recognize influencers as businesses (and many still have sexist notions &quot;influencer&quot; is vs &quot;creator,&quot; which are the same thing). I think as the space continues to grow in terms of $ more ppl will recognize it! https://t.co/iEoocBC5ng" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:21:32 GMT" tweetId="1409592821804244997" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409592821804244997" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="There are actually several LLCs called Instagram Husband or some version of that I'm sorry to report 😅 https://t.co/hQLdCJgvro https://t.co/cdWOclw5RZ" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:10:53 GMT" tweetId="1409590142864486401" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409590142864486401" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="FaZe Clan, Jeffree Star, MrBeast, Arielle Charnas and MANY more influencers received PPP loans. I know people don't like to think of it this way but creator-led companies are the fastest growing type of small business! https://t.co/ZGmePOwsnm" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:14:09 GMT" tweetId="1409590964570656768" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409590964570656768" inReplyToId="1409590142864486401" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Meet me by the 6-foot bronze Elon Musk statue in nyc https://t.co/rYWEXE9dMv" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 17:38:48 GMT" tweetId="1409566968617734147" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409566968617734147" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Bidding 1 zillion dollars so I can ship this statue to @kenklippenstein's living room  https://t.co/sjk70ZN1hh" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 18:13:29 GMT" tweetId="1409575696322600962" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409575696322600962" inReplyToId="1409566968617734147" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Are you a print reader? Donate your extra stacks of clean papers to the @wildbirdfund! https://t.co/rHkmSOXCI0" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 17:14:22 GMT" tweetId="1409560821546450944" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409560821546450944" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="You get a term sheet https://t.co/g6Pd6EceLd" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 17:05:55 GMT" tweetId="1409558694778392579" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409558694778392579" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Ppl need to understand that &quot;exposing/deep dive&quot; videos almost universally have an agenda, where things are twisted to fit a narrative and all &quot;evidence&quot; is in service of promoting that narrative. These videos mimic the language of reporting but are nothing like actual journalism https://t.co/obZr4PY181" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 16:51:35 GMT" tweetId="1409555085827268609" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409555085827268609" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I'd say generally don't trust anything you watch on YouTube. It's a lead distributor of conspiracy theories, propaganda, and disinfo. Try to read a book on the topic by an expert or go to verified sources like a reputable news outlet or expert in the space https://t.co/8Ew3dazGUF" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 17:01:09 GMT" tweetId="1409557493655638021" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409557493655638021" inReplyToId="1409555085827268609" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="Way too many young people blindly trust things they've seen on YouTube the way too many boomers trust everything they read on FB" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 17:13:07 GMT" tweetId="1409560506365472768" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409560506365472768" inReplyToId="1409557493655638021" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="How YouTube’s rules are used to silence human rights activists https://t.co/HJoXXLSh19" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 16:47:25 GMT" tweetId="1409554037037404164" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409554037037404164" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Setting an auto responder to, no you can not have 30 min on my calendar" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 15:55:53 GMT" tweetId="1409541070849904643" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409541070849904643" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is a must read https://t.co/dDJX2BJFPo" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 15:48:32 GMT" tweetId="1409539220213960708" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409539220213960708" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Thank you!! https://t.co/5uwABm2DPy" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 04:25:33 GMT" tweetId="1409367339531833345" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409367339531833345" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
