			<outline text="June 27" type="calendarDay" name="27" >
				<outline text="✌🏻✌🏻✌🏻 https://t.co/BTSxOeVB1F" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 02:25:26 GMT" tweetId="1409337112818683904" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409337112818683904" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I’ll be on the team too. Donate to @hchomeless and watch here: https://t.co/PZH8QhwxnF https://t.co/wktOYGf2LA" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 20:51:15 GMT" tweetId="1409253014284627969" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409253014284627969" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I’m playing Fortnite to benefit https://t.co/b3bPIqSHHU @hchomeless later today w/ @Kofie @mannyfidel @JordanUhl and more. 

You can donate to make us drop our weapons and basically ruin our chances of winning. Donate/watch: https://t.co/PZH8QhwxnF https://t.co/yeXftxnHlN" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 20:50:28 GMT" tweetId="1409252817479499783" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409252817479499783" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Happy birthday @kattenbarge!!! 💓🎉✨ https://t.co/6ybPxfXayr" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 16:10:53 GMT" tweetId="1409182457807527941" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409182457807527941" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 26" type="calendarDay" name="26" >
				<outline text="Can we bring Foursquare back this summer?????" type="tweet" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2021 02:15:07 GMT" tweetId="1408972128330809347" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408972128330809347" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Coming along well https://t.co/O8Auletx2N" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:39:08 GMT" tweetId="1408902676830572546" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408902676830572546" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Lol literally https://t.co/Vdtn25NKkL" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:30:32 GMT" tweetId="1408900509826576389" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408900509826576389" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Yup 🤦🏻‍♀️ https://t.co/iHSHvBDRBe" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:30:06 GMT" tweetId="1408900401714253825" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408900401714253825" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I totally agree TV news is bad too, it’s just not my realm of expertise. But yeah, there are huge flaws in our entire media ecosystem and people are left turning to randos on the internet to shape their worldview https://t.co/5CVW2NnZ3k" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:29:47 GMT" tweetId="1408900322685190144" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408900322685190144" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Ugh I’m so sorry :(. I feel like people understand that boomers are being radicalized this way but aren’t prepared for Gen Z, so many of whom treat YT as a primary news source and are more likely to trust influencers than traditional media https://t.co/zEOYwpPGSz" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:28:31 GMT" tweetId="1408900001179209730" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408900001179209730" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="It’s wild. Especially with the rise of all these anti media youtubers feigning as if they’re journalists. There seems to be an entire “aggrieved fired BuzzFeed employee to extremist propaganda social media personality” pipeline https://t.co/pFVnLaJIb9" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:18:36 GMT" tweetId="1408897505799020546" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408897505799020546" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="So terrifying how people today have zero media literacy. So many people tell me just absolutely wild and untrue lies and conspiracies, when I ask where they got it it’s almost always YouTube." type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:07:36 GMT" tweetId="1408894739923968000" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408894739923968000" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="There’s an increasing trend of YTers presenting disinfo and anti media conspiracy theories as “research” or “deep dives” or “investigations.” Of course they’re nothing of the sort, it’s absolutely made up lies or complete twisting of facts, usually for a politicized agenda." type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:10:16 GMT" tweetId="1408895408785432577" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408895408785432577" inReplyToId="1408894739923968000" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="Obviously big notable examples of this are the Plandemic video, but it happens so commonly in the influencer space. Lots of channels masking as “investigators” while presenting biased narratives or pushing conspiracies by mimicking the language of journalism" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:11:31 GMT" tweetId="1408895725383995393" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408895725383995393" inReplyToId="1408895408785432577" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="It’s terrifying to watch &amp;amp; generally impossible to disprove certain conspiracies b/c you’re stuck trying to prove a negative (Hillary Clinton isn’t raping children, for instance). People, including so many young ppl, fall for the YouTuber’s agenda hook line and sinker every time" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:14:52 GMT" tweetId="1408896568242049025" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408896568242049025" inReplyToId="1408895725383995393" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="A young man who works in tech was recently spreading videos accusing me of being a child predator and lying about what happened in Charlottesville as part of some deep state plan last week. When I confronted him he admitted he’d just seen it on YT and taken it as fact. Terrifying" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:22:10 GMT" tweetId="1408898404655067141" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408898404655067141" inReplyToId="1408896568242049025" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
									<outline text="Extremists &amp;amp; bad actors recognize that YT is fertile ground for smearing reporters and spreading propaganda and conspiracies. It’s just shocking to me how fast stuff migrates from Qanon forums, 4chan, etc to YouTube “researchers” and how many of them have become influencers" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 21:25:52 GMT" tweetId="1408899336709152771" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408899336709152771" inReplyToId="1408898404655067141" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Incredible full body cringe https://t.co/UfdjgFkEAS" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 20:46:09 GMT" tweetId="1408889341082955777" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408889341082955777" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="These influencer-promoted altcoin crypto scams are out of control, so rampant https://t.co/mwQ0RwfZFe" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 17:50:23 GMT" tweetId="1408845106166206471" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408845106166206471" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="“Everybody is just shit-scared and wanting to lie low. This is such a vindictive government.” https://t.co/NxXU4tNkwK" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 04:56:00 GMT" tweetId="1408650226974535681" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408650226974535681" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Trying to invite people to a party without FB events is misery. Like do u have to get everyone’s email?! Even though I was just talking about how IG is too much like FB I do wish they had an events tab 🙈" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 21:49:00 GMT" tweetId="1408542770826911746" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408542770826911746" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Ugh I’m too lazy for all this 😌 https://t.co/WR5m5QTtus" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 22:06:14 GMT" tweetId="1408547106051162116" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408547106051162116" inReplyToId="1408542770826911746" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Brooklyn is back 😌 https://t.co/0ZurGILUFt" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 21:22:40 GMT" tweetId="1408536143834931200" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408536143834931200" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Looks like that YouTubers vs TikTokers event didn’t do so well, the company behind it put out a statement in response to many creators who allege they still haven’t been paid. 
 
Company says it’s their “sincere hope” to be able to pay all the talent in a “reasonable timeframe” https://t.co/R8KM6zzhWg" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 21:15:15 GMT" tweetId="1408534275691991040" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408534275691991040" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="SCOOP: William White, who has gained a massive audience of older women by playing an 80s heartthrob on TikTok, has signed with WME https://t.co/xiyb5OfQFb" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 21:01:54 GMT" tweetId="1408530916092219393" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408530916092219393" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="William White has signed with IMG Modeling and WME talent agency, his manager will continue to manage him https://t.co/xiyb5OfQFb" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 21:05:47 GMT" tweetId="1408531892417097728" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408531892417097728" inReplyToId="1408530916092219393" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Thread https://t.co/sA5bRow00s" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:09:10 GMT" tweetId="1408457247080927240" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408457247080927240" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Got to collab with the brilliant @laurnosa on this story on TikTok, Black creators, and how the rise of the &quot;creator economy&quot; is reshaping people's views of creative labor https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:05:17 GMT" tweetId="1408456272806957065" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408456272806957065" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Instead trying to be hot I propose a slob girl summer https://t.co/poxrx7fq6l" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:40:27 GMT" tweetId="1408450020454531072" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408450020454531072" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Yeah that's one thing to note too, SO many dance trends on TikTok start internationally https://t.co/2QYDhK01JT" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:38:46 GMT" tweetId="1408449597165375489" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408449597165375489" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I wrote about the Black TikTok creator &quot;strike&quot; and shifting norms around labor and the creator economy https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:08:11 GMT" tweetId="1408441901489950722" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408441901489950722" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="To frame this as an issue around dance credits misses the point. It's about so much more &amp;amp; speaks to broader issues of labor in the creator econ. “We are being exploited, and that’s the core issue Black folks have always had in terms of labor,” Erick said https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:12:39 GMT" tweetId="1408443024745533455" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408443024745533455" inReplyToId="1408441901489950722" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="“These millions of likes, that should all translate to something. How do we get real money, power and proper compensation we deserve?” https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:13:07 GMT" tweetId="1408443141695234055" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408443141695234055" inReplyToId="1408443024745533455" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="“The strike to send a message. The business models of these apps, they have us out here overworking and being underpaid. We’re working long hours but at the end of the day we’re still making little to nothing, and we Black creators are making even less.” https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:13:47 GMT" tweetId="1408443311694565376" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408443311694565376" inReplyToId="1408443141695234055" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="“My hope is that we realize this is an entire class of work that didn’t previously exist,” said @ljin18. “If we don’t offer this class of workers protections and rights, they’re going to become increasingly disenfranchised.” https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:15:19 GMT" tweetId="1408443697746702337" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408443697746702337" inReplyToId="1408443311694565376" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
									<outline text="@ljin18 Creators, especially Black creators, are finally recognizing the value they generate for these multi billion dollar tech companies and are asking for more https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa https://t.co/Pra8Gc489R" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:17:35 GMT" tweetId="1408444266481786883" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408444266481786883" inReplyToId="1408443697746702337" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
										<outline text="@ljin18 Kaelyn Kastle, a Black creator in Atlanta put it this way, &quot;We're working so hard to sustain these apps while trying to build something for ourselves and getting little to nothing out of it. These apps expect us to be happy with just building an audience.&quot; https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:18:48 GMT" tweetId="1408444573102133251" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408444573102133251" inReplyToId="1408444266481786883" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
											<outline text="Even before the &quot;strike,&quot; dance trends on TikTok have been declining &amp;amp; the trends associated with many top audios have not included dances. Despite tweets suggesting otherwise, the trend most popularly associated w/ Thot Shit was never dance related. https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:22:46 GMT" tweetId="1408445572181204992" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408445572181204992" inReplyToId="1408444573102133251" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
												<outline text="TikToks top creators have transitioned away from dancing toward more vlogging and YouTube-style content. As the pandemic wanes, average users are also spending more time outside their homes creating a more diverse range of content as the app evolves https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:24:12 GMT" tweetId="1408445931045806083" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408445931045806083" inReplyToId="1408445572181204992" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
													<outline text="“The shift away from dance takes even more of the megaphone away from these Black creators,” said Kwasi Ohene-Adu, the founder of Groovetime, a platform for creators to own and monetize their dances. https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:30:59 GMT" tweetId="1408447640962961408" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408447640962961408" inReplyToId="1408445931045806083" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
													</outline>
												</outline>
											</outline>
										</outline>
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			</outline>
